<chapter id="exception-handling">
    <title>Exception Handling</title>
    <para>
        Exception handling is a very important mechanism in enterprise applications that is used for eg. to show 
        friendly messages to end user when something went wrong.
            
        To enable exception handling in 
        <emphasis>Conventions </emphasis> you must add the following lines to your faces-config.xml file:
    </para>
    <programlisting role="XML"><![CDATA[ 
     <faces-config version="2.0" xmlns="http://java.sun.com/xml/ns/javaee"
	xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
	xsi:schemaLocation="http://java.sun.com/xml/ns/javaee http://java.sun.com/xml/ns/javaee/web-facesconfig_2_0.xsd">
            <application>
                 <action-listener>org.conventionsframework.exception.ConventionsActionListenerImpl</action-listener>
             </application>
      </faces-config>
             ]]>
    </programlisting>
        
